A rubik's cube has 6 faces (WHITE, YELLOW, RED, ORANGE, GREEN, BLUE)
- WHITE and YELLOW are opposites
- RED and ORANGE
- GREEN and BLUE

WHITE = 1
RED = 2
BLUE = 3
YELLOW = 4
ORANGE = 5
GREEN = 6

Each face has 8 moving pieces, shared with other faces
- 4 edge pieces, each shared with one other face
- 4 corner pieces, each shared with two other faces

When turn occurs, face rotates, neighboring faces update array accordingly


CLASSES
- Cube
    - has: 6 faces
    - interface
- Face
    - has: EdgePiece[], CornerPiece[]
    - turning function (clockwise and counterclockwise)
- EdgePiece
    - has: int[] with 2 colors
- CornerPiece
    - has: int[] with 3 colors (clockwise permutation)